0.10    2016-02-20 (PERLANCAR)

        - Split each list into a separate module (POD) to help 'lcpan
          related-mods' result. When a POD document mentions unrelated modules
          together (which is when several unrelated lists are put together in a
          single POD), it gives a false positive for the 'lcpan related-mods'
          result which thinks that such modules are related. To help 'lcpan
          related-mods', I now put each list into a separate POD.

        - Add module list: Getting system-wide temporary directory in a portable
          way.

        - Add module list: Assertion.

        - Mention about BackPAN or GitHub on how to get retired modules.

        [REMOVED]

        - Remove test lists.


